The Group Managing Director of NNPC, Kolo Mele Kyari will this afternoon, at the Teslim Balogun stadium, Surulere, Lagos declare the 18th Nigeria Oil and Gas Industry Games closed. Kyari will be assisted by captains and movers of the Nigerian energy sector, including top management staff of the participating companies. We gathered that the Minister of state in the Ministry of Petroleum, Timipre Marlin Sylva and the Governor of Lagos State, Babajide Sanwo-0lu will be ably represented at the event billed to kick off as early as 10 in the morning. Chairman, Local Organising Committee, Aminu Zaria said the games have been very successful as everything has gone as planned and above all, “the athletes have been well behaved and there was no injury during the week-long event. He disclosed that the closing ceremony will be spiced up by cultural displays that will depict Nigeria’s diversity, adding that, “it will be a spectacle.” Zaria who spoke on the games with our correspondent observed that “the NOGIG 2020 has been the most competitive in recent years as almost all the participating companies are going home with medals. “It has been a different story this year as the medals were equitably distributes, unlike in previous editions where you find some companies giving others very wide gaps in the medal table. It is no longer business as usual. The LOC boss said the games have been very entertaining because of the level of competition among the participating companies as those who, in the past were not doing well have gone back to do their homework. In some of the events decided yesterday, five-time table tennis   final, Obinna Iloeje of NNPC defeated Bere Barien of Chevron to win the gold medal. Copyright PUNCH.
